<template>
<div class="wrap">
  <img src="https://blog.codepen.io/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Made-For-Codepen.png" alt="" />
  
  <p>
    Hi there, <br /> <br />
    A while ago I made a Chrome 'Extension' and I thought you, might want it too.
  </p>
<ol>
  <li>Create a folder</li>
  <li>Copy the code in the JS Tab</li>
  <li>Create a file named <code>manifest.json</code></li>
  <li>Download on of the Codepen logos <a href="https://blog.codepen.io/documentation/brand-assets/logos/" target="_blank">here</a></li>
  <li>Save it as <code>codepen.png</code> and put that in the folder as well</li>
  <li>Go to <code>chrome://extentions</code> (Menu > Tools > Extensions</li>
  <li>Click <code>Load unpacked extention...</code></li>
  <li>Select the folder</li>
  <li>Open a new tab and see you shortcut :)</li>
  <li>Have fun!</li>
</ol>  
</div>
</template>

<script>
export default {
    name: "Popup"
}
</script>

